    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh convergence study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh refinement levels (coarse: ~28 000 elements, medium: ~72 000 elements, fine: ~185 000 elements, and very fine: ~410 000 elements) were evaluated. Construct stiffness and yield force QoIs were monitored across refinement levels. The Richardson extrapolation-based Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed for each QoI. Results indicated GCI < 1.2% for stiffness and < 0.9% for yield force at the fine mesh level, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds. The fine mesh was selected as the production mesh for all subsequent validation simulations.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
